Emir of Fika and Chairman Yobe State Council of Traditional Rulers Dr. Muhammad Ibn Abali Muhammad Idrissa has urged Nigerians to intensify prayers and support for unity and peace in the country. In a press statement signed by Alhaji Mohammed Abubakar, Special Adviser Media to the Monarch appealed to Nigerians to embrace one another and bury the political, religious and tribal differences to enable Nigeria to continue to live peacefully. “As traditional leaders, we will continue to support the government with intensive prayers through our subjects, we consider Nigeria first before any other thing, it is our Country that we need to improve our patriotism, selflessness and peaceful coexistence”. New Year: Aliyu Donates Delivery Kits To 600 Mothers, Pays… Yuletide: Niger CP Felicitates With Christians, Assures Of… “We’re also appealing to our Youths to stay clear of drugs and any form of criminality, instead engage in skills and entrepreneurship to earn them meaningful living”. He emphasized that the safety of lives and property in all parts of the Country would remain their priority.